---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL, SITE_NAME } from '~/consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`About ${SITE_NAME}: what this site is, who runs it, and why we're building another JSON beautifier in the first place.`}
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About {SITE_NAME}</h1>

    <p>
      {SITE_NAME} is an independent, ad-supported developer utility.
      Our goal is simple: a fast, accurate, privacy-respecting way to format,
      minify, and validate JSON — with XML and HTML to follow — combined with
      short, honest explanations of what each format actually is.
    </p>

    <h2>What makes this different</h2>
    <p>
      Every major "JSON formatter" site is battling two problems at once:
      they need to make money, and they are competing with a crowded market.
      That usually ends with aggressive ad stacks, slow pages on mobile, or
      both. We took a different approach:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>No ads in the first fold of the tool itself.</strong> If
        you're here to debug a broken API response, you should be able to see
        the error on line 47 without scrolling past a leaderboard.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>All parsing happens on your device.</strong> JSON.parse runs
        inside a dedicated Web Worker in your browser. We don't have a server
        that sees your inputs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Each format comes with a guide.</strong> If you're new to JSON
        Schema or JSONL, we'd rather give you a 3-minute read than send you
        back to search results.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who runs this</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE_NAME} is a one-person project operated from South Korea as part of
      a portfolio of small, focused web utilities. It is not affiliated with
      Google, any ad network, or any specific JSON parser. If you want to get
      in touch, use the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or email us at
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>How it's built</h2>
    <p>
      The site is a static Astro build served by Nginx on an Oracle Cloud
      Always Free instance. The JSON engine runs in a browser Web Worker so
      the main thread stays responsive even when you paste a 5&nbsp;MB payload.
      There is no user account, no tracking pixel for your inputs, and no
      third-party analytics of your JSON. See the
      <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for the full picture.
    </p>

    <h2>Roadmap in brief</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>JSON tool with beautify / minify / validate / sort keys — <em>available now</em></li>
      <li>Guides &amp; glossary for JSON fundamentals — <em>in progress</em></li>
      <li>XML and HTML beautifiers — <em>next</em></li>
      <li>REST API for large payloads (&gt; 10&nbsp;MB) — <em>later</em></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Support the project</h2>
    <p>
      If this tool saves you time, the best thing you can do is tell a teammate
      about it. Ad revenue funds the server bill; good word-of-mouth funds the
      motivation to keep it fast and ad-light.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
